  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The ARCADIA cognitive architecture is composed primarily of a collection of non-introspectable processing units called components.",
    "On each ARCADIA processing cycle, components may take in and produce interlingua content items, which are tables of labeled data able to be interpreted by other components.",
    "Once generated, content items are placed in an accessible content area from which the architecture will select one on each processing cycle to become the focus of attention.",
    "This selected element is fed back into the components and used to generate more content items.",
    "The strategy for selecting a content item is decided on a task-to-task basis that favors items, representing things deserving of more attention, such as those representing changes to objects within the field of vision."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}